<!-- banner part start-->
<section class="banner_part">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-5 col-xl-5">
                <div class="banner_text">
                    <div class="banner_text_iner">
                        <h5></h5>
                        <h1>Chairman's Speech</h1>
                        <p>
                            NUJ Oyo State has 10 chapels at the moment which is led by Comrade Ademola Babalola, the chapels are the units that constituted a state council.They are the media houses where members of the union are drawn.
                            <br />
                            With the press centre  situated at Iyaganku GRA in Ibadan, the following are the corresponding chapels: Federal Information, State Information, Tribune, Inspiration FM, Oke-Ogun, FRCN(Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria), BCOS(Broadcasting Corporation of Oyo State),  ALGIO(Association of Local Government Information Officers), and NTA(Nigerian Television Authority).
                        </p>

                        <!-- <a href="#" class="btn_2">Are you a panelist?</a> -->

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <div class="banner_img">
                    <img src="~/img/excos/chairman.jpg" alt="">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<!-- banner part start-->

<!-- about us part start-->
<section class="about_us padding_top">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-between align-items-center">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6">
                <div class="about_us_img">
                    <img src="~/img/about-us-home.jpg" alt="Homepage about">
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-5">
                <div class="about_us_text">

                    <h2>About Association</h2>

                    <p>
                        Emergence of journalists’ agitation in Nigeria, which eventually led to the formation of a virile Union, Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), is as old as the struggle for Independence itself. Most notable statesmen, who fought for self rule and extinct of Colonialism were Journalists/Politicians.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Oyo State Council of Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), after its formation in the early 50 – 60s, experienced serious intimidation of its members, aftermath of the political instability in the Western region.
                    </p>

                    @Html.ActionLink("Read More", "about", null, new { @class = "genric-btn success-border circle" })
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
